summary: Email chain between a paralegal specialist at the U.S. Attorney's Office SDNY and an FBI Special Agent regarding technical assistance with '.anb' file extensions encountered during document production for the Ghislaine Maxwell case. The paralegal is working on deduplication for the 'Maxwell 3500' production and seeks expertise on how to view files created in IBM 'analyst notebook' software.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The email chain references document production work for 'Maxwell 3500', indicating she is the central figure in the case for which these files are being processed.

persons.name: Special Agent
persons.context: An FBI Special Agent from the New York Field Office, Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking Desk, responds to a technical inquiry about '.anb' files, indicating they are consulting with Intel Analysts.

persons.name: Paralegal Specialist
persons.context: A paralegal specialist at the U.S. Attorney's Office SDNY emails FBI contacts seeking technical assistance with '.anb' file extensions encountered while deduplicating files for the Maxwell case production.

connections.description: The paralegal specialist reaches out to the FBI Special Agent for technical assistance regarding file formats encountered in the Maxwell case document production.
The paralegal specialist is working on document production ('Maxwell 3500') related to the legal case against Ghislaine Maxwell.
The FBI Special Agent, part of the Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking Desk, is involved in the investigation or support related to the Ghislaine Maxwell case.

events.title: Technical inquiry about .anb files
events.description: A paralegal specialist at the U.S. Attorney's Office SDNY sends an email inquiring about experience with '.anb' file extensions encountered during document production for the Maxwell case.

events.title: FBI response on .anb files
events.description: An FBI Special Agent responds to the technical inquiry, indicating they are not familiar with the '.anb' format but believe it is from an older program used by Intel Analysts and will consult with them.

locations: 1 Saint Andrew's Plaza, New York, NY 10007
keyFacts: Document production for the Ghislaine Maxwell case (referred to as 'Maxwell 3500') was ongoing as of September 2021.
Investigators encountered technical challenges with '.anb' file extensions, which are associated with IBM 'analyst notebook' software, potentially used for intelligence analysis.
The U.S. Attorney's Office SDNY and FBI New York Field Office's Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking Desk were collaborating on technical aspects of the case.
The email chain demonstrates ongoing post-conviction investigative work and evidence processing related to the Maxwell case.
